org.la4j.vector

Interface Vector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Externalizable, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DenseVector, SparseVector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractVector, BasicVector, CompressedVector

    public interface Vector
extends Externalizable
    The real vector interface.

      • norm

        @Deprecated
double norm()
        Deprecated. 
        Calculates the Euclidean norm of this vector. This method is deprecated. Use the following approach instead: Vector a = ...; double norm0 = a.fold(Vectors.mkEuclideanNormAccumulator()); double norm1 = a.fold(Vectors.mkManhattanNormAccumulator()); double normInf = a.fold(Vectors.mkInfinityNormAccumulator());
        Returns:
        the Euclidean norm of this vector

      • normalize

        @Deprecated
Vector normalize()
        Deprecated. 
        Normalizes this vector. This method is deprecated. Use the following approach instead: Vector a = ...; double norm1 = a.fold(Vectors.mkManhattanNormAccumulator()); Vector b = a.divide(norm1);
        Returns:
        the normalized vector

      • shuffle

        Vector shuffle()
        Shuffles this vector.

        Copies this vector in the new vector that contains the same elements but with the elements shuffled around (which might also result in the same vector (all outcomes are equally probable)).

        Returns:
        the shuffled vector
